[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return redacted
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _emit_event(detail_type: str, detail: dict) -> None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Emit an EventBridge event. Wrapped in try/except so a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     transient EventBridge failure does not block the chat
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     handler. Production downstream consumers should use the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     suggested idempotency keys (engagement_id, decision_id,
