[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1956[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1957[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The engagement scheduler is the most operationally subtle piece of the architecture. Most teams that build a chronic-coach for the first time underestimate how much policy lives in this layer. Production runs this as a Step Functions workflow with delay states (so the durable scheduling survives Lambda outages and region failover), with the engagement-policy enforcement re-checked at each delivery time (the patient may have changed preferences since the engagement was scheduled), with fatigue detection running on a rolling 30-day window, and with explicit fatigue-mitigation logic that reduces cadence when response rates drop below the floor.
